1.99 per pound.

03:27.082 --> 03:30.419
Pound. Make sure
you hit the "D" on the end of pound.

03:30.585 --> 03:34.214
"Where she buy some coffee."

03:38.719 --> 03:41.304
God. Can you believe
these are still in bloom?

03:41.596 --> 03:44.182
Oh! Those are nice.

03:44.266 --> 03:46.393
I can put these on your table if you like.

03:46.476 --> 03:47.811
I don’t care. It’s up to you.

03:51.022 --> 03:53.442
So, uh, how’s it going?

03:53.984 --> 03:55.277
Good. I’m just kind of tired.

03:56.611 --> 03:59.781
It’s only 11, Preston.
Are you enjoying it at least?

03:59.865 --> 04:02.534
- Yeah. I like it a lot, actually.
- Oh, good.

04:03.034 --> 04:06.329
Are you going to go to the Ashford’s
tonight? Just for old time's sake?

04:06.872 --> 04:08.957
Uh... I’m good.

04:12.127 --> 04:14.212
Can a mother still kiss her son?

04:20.927 --> 04:22.047
It’s so fun having you here.

04:22.137 --> 04:24.264
I’m very proud of you.
Everyone likes you.

04:24.347 --> 04:27.058
- Yeah, well, they kind of have to.
- No. That’s not true.

04:28.185 --> 04:30.312
- Never mind. I guess it’s true...
- All right.

04:48.997 --> 04:51.833
Hi, there. I’m Sandy, if you need anything.

04:52.626 --> 04:55.545
- That’s great, isn’t it?
- Well...

04:55.629 --> 04:57.005
Is this a real lobster trap?

04:57.255 --> 05:00.801
No. No. But trust me,
you wouldn’t want it if it was.

05:00.967 --> 05:03.970
Makes a nice decorative
accent though, don’t you think?

05:04.429 --> 05:06.681
I’m looking for things
to put on my shelves.

05:07.349 --> 05:09.351
Oh! You have a new place?

05:09.559 --> 05:10.559
Yeah.

05:11.144 --> 05:12.144
Starting over.

05:12.521 --> 05:15.982
- Taking the day off work, I guess?
- Oh, no. No...

05:17.818 --> 05:19.236
Actually, I’m retired.

05:19.903 --> 05:21.238
- Really?
- Yeah.

05:29.079 --> 05:30.288
I think it’s out.

05:30.580 --> 05:32.082
No, it’s good. I think it’s...

05:36.628 --> 05:40.090
I don’t know what’s wrong with me.
This never happens to me.

05:40.840 --> 05:42.551
I mean, this is not your fault.

05:42.634 --> 05:44.074
I didn’t think that it was my fault.

05:44.302 --> 05:45.720
Good. Because it’s not.

05:45.804 --> 05:46.805
Right. I know.

06:23.216 --> 06:24.216
Anders?

06:25.552 --> 06:28.513
You came. A surprise.

06:29.180 --> 06:31.308
Yeah. Thanks for inviting me.

06:31.391 --> 06:34.436
Of course. Why don’t you grab yourself
a drink in the other room?

06:43.987 --> 06:44.987
Wes.

06:46.948 --> 06:48.533
I heard you got out of finance.

06:48.908 --> 06:49.951
I’m jealous.

06:50.076 --> 06:51.076
Well...

06:51.828 --> 06:53.997
Quit your job, Wes.
That’s all you gotta do.

06:54.414 --> 06:55.957
You make it sound so easy.

06:56.333 --> 06:57.459
I mean...

06:57.751 --> 07:00.629
You’re a relatively young guy.
Why get out so early?

07:00.837 --> 07:03.590
- Do you really want to know?
- Sure.

07:04.966 --> 07:05.966
Let me have it.

07:06.259 --> 07:07.259
Well...

07:07.802 --> 07:12.015
It’s a system of monstrous greed,
and that’s the business.

07:12.849 --> 07:14.017
Save yourself.

07:14.851 --> 07:16.478
Do over the other guy.

07:16.770 --> 07:20.023
And don’t worry about the consequences.
And for what?

07:20.774 --> 07:22.817
More toys? Bigger houses?

07:22.901 --> 07:26.571
Trip to the goddamn Caribbean?
Fake titties? No, thank you.

07:27.405 --> 07:28.525
So, you have some big plans?

07:29.282 --> 07:30.283
Yeah, I’m doing, uh...

07:30.367 --> 07:33.203
I'm doing a little decorating
at the moment. You know, condo living.

07:33.370 --> 07:36.081
- You enjoying that?
- Not at all. Would you?

07:36.164 --> 07:37.499
I wouldn’t retire.

07:38.833 --> 07:41.252
Well, I also got some, you know,
charity work going on.

07:41.336 --> 07:42.587
- Oh? Which one?
- Yeah.

07:43.338 --> 07:48.343
Uh... Disease. Diseases.
You know, in the cancer spectrum.

07:52.806 --> 07:54.766
What the hell is he doing here?

07:55.141 --> 07:57.310
I just saw him ear raping Wes Thompson.

07:57.394 --> 07:58.812
Well, just...

07:59.354 --> 08:02.816
The one time he doesn’t have to be here,
in fact shouldn’t be here, and here he is.

08:02.899 --> 08:04.043
I shouldn’t have sent him the invite.

08:04.067 --> 08:06.361
He was on the list.
I wasn’t paying attention.

08:06.444 --> 08:09.531
It’s okay. It's just... He makes me sad.

08:10.699 --> 08:12.909
You look really pretty, by the way.

08:13.326 --> 08:14.411
You’re having sex.

08:15.245 --> 08:16.496
Yes. That is true.

08:18.039 --> 08:20.208
Just... not as good as with Anders?

08:20.792 --> 08:22.210
Well, you know...

08:23.420 --> 08:27.382
Why do we do this every year?
Our fucking kids don’t even come.

08:27.632 --> 08:29.259
Kat’s not even coming for Christmas.

08:29.884 --> 08:31.886
Are you kid... That’s awful.

08:32.136 --> 08:33.679
Why didn’t Preston come?

08:34.014 --> 08:36.307
You know, Preston had other plans.

08:36.765 --> 08:38.101
Whatever that means.

08:38.684 --> 08:41.312
- Oh God, I hate these fucking Spanx.
- Mmm.

08:53.199 --> 08:54.075
Hello.

08:54.159 --> 08:56.661
Shh...

09:00.957 --> 09:02.542
- Hey.
- Yo. What’s up?

09:03.585 --> 09:05.754
- What are you guys smoking?
- What?

09:05.837 --> 09:08.465
You don’t have to worry.
I’m not gonna tell anyone.

09:08.548 --> 09:10.108
You’re gonna be doing it anyway, right?

09:10.175 --> 09:14.054
If you’re one of my dad’s friends that he
sent out here to narc on us or whatever,

09:14.137 --> 09:17.515
you can go back in and tell him
that he’s very sad and predictable.

09:17.682 --> 09:18.933
Okay, Charlie.

09:19.517 --> 09:20.517
Who is that?

09:21.352 --> 09:23.730
- Anders.
- Oh, Christ...

09:23.813 --> 09:25.523
And I’m not one of your dad’s friends.

09:25.607 --> 09:27.942
Wait, dude, come back for a sec.
Come here.

09:28.943 --> 09:30.383
What do you mean you’re not friends?

09:31.821 --> 09:35.742
Well, I’m not.
I mean my wife is. Well, my ex-wife.

09:37.035 --> 09:39.829
Personally, I can’t, uh...
I can't stand your parents.

09:39.913 --> 09:42.207
I find them unbearable.

09:42.290 --> 09:46.252
Really? After all those summers
and shitty dinners

09:46.419 --> 09:47.754
and blah blah blah?

09:47.837 --> 09:49.422
I walked away from all that.

09:49.506 --> 09:50.757
So I’ve heard.

09:51.883 --> 09:53.176
So, why are you here?

09:53.259 --> 09:56.513
That’s a really fucking good question.

09:56.596 --> 09:57.931
You know how to rip one of these?

09:58.640 --> 10:00.266
I don’t even know what that is.

10:00.350 --> 10:02.435
This... is resourceful.

10:05.855 --> 10:06.855
Come on.

10:06.898 --> 10:10.276
Yeah, yeah. Okay. Sure, why not? Fuck it.

10:12.278 --> 10:13.571
There you go.

10:14.239 --> 10:15.490
Thank you.

10:17.325 --> 10:18.368
- Hi.
- Hey.

10:24.916 --> 10:26.501
Whoa. Whoa. Whoa. Okay. Damn.

10:35.176 --> 10:38.805
Yeah, the smell of your dad’s cigar...

10:41.683 --> 10:43.518
makes me wish I was born without a face.

10:47.689 --> 10:48.689
How you feeling?

10:50.942 --> 10:53.486
Oh, wow. Oh, yeah...

10:55.905 --> 10:58.032
Oh. I feel joyful.

10:58.783 --> 11:00.910
Oh. So joy... Wow.

11:05.665 --> 11:09.586
And sad, too... Jesus.

11:10.128 --> 11:13.172
This is some serious grass.

11:13.798 --> 11:14.799
Nah. That’s the PCP.

11:16.593 --> 11:17.593
Yeah.

11:17.677 --> 11:20.054
What, are you joking? I just smoked PCP?

11:20.138 --> 11:21.848
We don’t technically know what it is.

11:22.056 --> 11:23.683
- It’s like more of a blend.
- Yeah!

11:23.766 --> 11:26.936
We feel joyful.

11:27.145 --> 11:28.354
So joyful.

11:28.646 --> 11:30.273
- And sad.
- Very sad.

11:35.528 --> 11:37.864
I should get back to the party.

11:37.989 --> 11:40.491
All right. Knock yourself out. Have fun.

11:40.700 --> 11:42.410
Be careful, man.

11:49.667 --> 11:51.669
Oh. What’re you doing out here, buddy?

11:51.753 --> 11:54.130
Oh, just getting some air.

11:58.593 --> 12:00.094
You’ve had a big year, huh?

12:00.970 --> 12:04.557
- Surprised to see you here.
- Yeah. Thank you.

12:05.516 --> 12:07.977
- I'm still looking for my son.
- Yeah.

12:08.353 --> 12:11.397
Disappeared earlier,
which is cause for worry.

12:11.481 --> 12:13.083
He was supposed to be
in his room studying,

12:13.107 --> 12:16.402
as he failed three
of his exams at his boarding school.

12:17.445 --> 12:20.490
I’m so fucking sick of warning him.

12:20.740 --> 12:21.950
Who am I talking to?

12:22.033 --> 12:23.660
- You know better than anyone.
- Yeah.

12:23.743 --> 12:28.039
No, seriously, with Preston,
you guys, you did a program, right?

12:28.289 --> 12:29.289
Huh?

12:29.415 --> 12:31.175
You drag him off into the woods
or something?

12:31.209 --> 12:32.961
Or something. Yeah.

12:34.253 --> 12:35.421
Excuse me.

12:47.308 --> 12:49.352
- I don’t get it.
- Look who it is.

12:51.062 --> 12:53.782
- I don’t get it.
- Okay. Let’s come over here for a minute.

13:00.029 --> 13:04.367
So... are you seeing that guy now?

13:05.243 --> 13:06.577
Yeah. For a few months, yeah.

13:06.911 --> 13:09.622
And is he gonna live here now?

13:09.706 --> 13:11.958
Uh, well, he’s looking for a place.

13:12.041 --> 13:15.169
He’s, uh, trying to get out of the city.
He’s going to commute for a while.

13:15.253 --> 13:18.464
And what... you guys have been sleeping
together for a couple of years now?

13:18.548 --> 13:19.424
Please don’t.

13:19.507 --> 13:21.968
What, have we been divorced
for, like, six months?

13:22.635 --> 13:24.512
Honey, why are you at this party?

13:25.471 --> 13:26.764
I was invited.

13:27.306 --> 13:29.058
Everyone’s invited.

13:40.528 --> 13:43.364
- Do you think this is funny?
- No, I don’t...

13:46.325 --> 13:47.618
That is funny.

13:49.120 --> 13:50.413
What is wrong with you, Anders?

13:50.872 --> 13:52.999
You are the one
who said you needed space.

13:53.332 --> 13:56.753
Well, it’s not my job anymore.
I don’t have to babysit you.

13:57.462 --> 13:59.922
I don’t have to make sure
that you don’t embarrass yourself.

14:00.006 --> 14:03.885
You are the one who wanted out.
So, for God fucking sake, get out.

14:03.968 --> 14:05.048
We need an ambulance!

14:05.345 --> 14:07.764
- Somebody call an ambulance!
- Oh, my God!

14:12.351 --> 14:13.511
<i>Fucking angel dust?</i>

14:14.270 --> 14:16.790
I heard they got him hooked up
to a bunch of tubes and machines.

14:18.149 --> 14:20.234
Mom said Sophie is a complete wreck.

14:20.318 --> 14:21.402
I’m sure she is.

14:22.111 --> 14:24.072
Apparently, the Ashfords are suing now.

14:26.157 --> 14:28.159
Who in God’s name are they gonna sue?

14:28.242 --> 14:31.371
Uh, the school, I guess. I mean,
they think that’s where he got the drugs.

14:31.454 --> 14:32.330
Wait, wait.

14:32.413 --> 14:35.500
They move their kid
to a different school because of drug use,

14:35.583 --> 14:38.294
and now they’re blaming
his current drug use

14:38.378 --> 14:40.421
on the school that they shipped him to?

14:40.505 --> 14:43.549
Don’t act like you don’t understand it.
You guys did the same thing to me.

14:43.633 --> 14:44.926
I didn’t sue anybody.

14:45.009 --> 14:48.429
And you went to rehab.
Not boarding school.

14:48.513 --> 14:51.516
- Well, I feel bad for the kid.
- So do I.

14:52.141 --> 14:53.810
Hey, I heard you saw Mom.

14:54.185 --> 14:57.230
- And met her new boyfriend?
- Yeah. I already knew him.

14:57.438 --> 14:59.732
- You did?
- Mm-hmm. Not well.

14:59.857 --> 15:01.442
We came up together as traders.

15:05.405 --> 15:07.615
Just tell me he’s not living at the house.

15:07.782 --> 15:09.367
Well, it’s Mom’s house. So...

15:12.078 --> 15:13.496
He’s living at the house?

15:15.206 --> 15:16.526
Dad, it’s not your house anymore.

15:16.666 --> 15:19.377
- Well, it's certainly not theirs.
- What does that mean?

15:20.711 --> 15:21.712
Isn’t it Mom’s?

15:21.963 --> 15:25.133
Well, it was going to be. Yeah...

15:25.216 --> 15:31.139
but in a fit of generosity and stupidity,
I told her she could have it.

15:31.722 --> 15:38.062
But I can’t afford to retire
and pay for the mortgage.

15:39.147 --> 15:40.231
Jesus.

15:42.108 --> 15:44.610
- Don’t tell your mother, okay?
- You know, Mom’s gonna freak.

15:45.278 --> 15:46.696
Where the fuck am I gonna live?

15:46.779 --> 15:50.241
You living there is meant to be temporary.

15:51.826 --> 15:53.911
She should downsize anyway.

15:54.996 --> 15:56.998
- Hell, let Donny pay for it.
- Well...

15:57.415 --> 15:59.333
I guess he probably can.
He seems pretty loaded.

16:02.128 --> 16:03.128
Well...

16:06.299 --> 16:09.219
I don’t know, Dad. I mean, it looks like
a bunch of little kids live here.

16:10.595 --> 16:13.639
Eh. Look at it. It’s nice. It’s festive.

16:15.141 --> 16:17.226
It’s like your own sad
little Christmas parade.

16:20.229 --> 16:21.564
All right. Gotta go.

16:30.781 --> 16:33.034
Wow, do you think this is a bit much?

16:35.828 --> 16:38.915
Thanks so much. Of course, I will.

16:39.499 --> 16:40.791
Oh, you know it.

16:41.375 --> 16:44.003
He’s going as soon as he’s out.
We’ve found a good place.

16:44.795 --> 16:47.215
Yes. I will. Thanks again.

16:48.674 --> 16:50.176
Oh, honey, you’re so nice.

16:50.259 --> 16:51.552
I'm not really that nice.

16:52.470 --> 16:54.630
I just couldn’t imagine
who I’d run into at the market.

16:54.680 --> 16:56.933
Well, you would have run
into Aunt Marilyn Erickson...

16:57.016 --> 16:59.227
- Oof.
- ...and Leslie Abrams. Separately.

16:59.685 --> 17:01.062
You’re my savior.

17:05.733 --> 17:07.944
- Thank you.
- Yes, you’re welcome.

17:09.737 --> 17:11.714
How long do you think
Preston’s gonna stay with you?

17:11.739 --> 17:14.407
Jesus. There’s a part of me,
the sick part,

17:14.617 --> 17:16.077
kinda likes having him around.

17:16.160 --> 17:17.304
Every once in a while I forget

17:17.328 --> 17:19.579
and I go to, like,
move something out of his face,

17:19.664 --> 17:23.376
and he... One of these things.
It’s like, "Oh. Oh, right, you’re a man."

17:24.961 --> 17:26.087
What did we do wrong?

17:26.671 --> 17:28.047
Maybe I babied him too much.

17:29.465 --> 17:30.905
Perhaps we’ve done everything wrong.

17:32.218 --> 17:34.018
When are we gonna know
if our kids are broken?

17:36.013 --> 17:37.974
Gee, let’s see. What time is it?

17:38.099 --> 17:40.768
Tell me about your week. The holidays.

17:40.935 --> 17:43.771
Uh... I got the condo decorated.

17:43.854 --> 17:46.065
Uh... Preston helped.

17:46.566 --> 17:49.860
- That must have been nice.
- And I, uh, went to a party.

17:50.069 --> 17:52.280
I don’t know why I went.

17:53.573 --> 17:56.659
Yeah, I do. I went to see Helene. Uh...

17:56.909 --> 17:58.494
Was an awful night. I, uh...

17:59.203 --> 18:02.081
I ended up getting very loaded.
It did not go well.

18:02.415 --> 18:04.500
- You got loaded?
- Yeah. I did a stupid thing.

18:04.959 --> 18:08.379
I got high with a bunch of kids
and then one of them ended up in the ER.

18:09.297 --> 18:11.757
- You got high with the kids?
- Stupid.

18:11.966 --> 18:14.594
At this point, Anders,
I should tell you. I was...

18:15.428 --> 18:17.054
I was at the Ashford’s party.

18:18.139 --> 18:19.390
Hmm?

18:19.473 --> 18:21.392
I'm... I don't... I'm not... Sorry.

18:21.642 --> 18:23.894
Kathleen and Sophie Ashford
are quite close.

18:24.812 --> 18:27.273
Oh, well, I didn’t see you there.

18:29.108 --> 18:30.443
So, uh...

18:31.777 --> 18:35.781
So, okay, so you know what happened
to Charlie.

18:35.865 --> 18:40.077
And, um... Uh, Jesus...

18:40.786 --> 18:43.372
Way to bury the lead, Howard. Okay.

18:43.456 --> 18:47.710
Uh... Well, I’m sure that you know...

18:48.210 --> 18:51.130
I’m sure Charlie’s gonna be all right.
I mean...

18:51.213 --> 18:55.092
Kids smoke dope,
and it’s not a big deal.

18:55.718 --> 18:57.762
Do you know what drugs he was doing?

18:58.220 --> 19:00.097
It was some kind of high school...

19:00.598 --> 19:04.101
boarding school,
kind of hybrid blend kind of thing.

19:04.185 --> 19:06.687
- Maybe PCP.
- PCP?

19:07.938 --> 19:11.108
Look, he hands me this thing,
crazy little device,

19:11.192 --> 19:15.154
I thought it was grass,
and yeah, it was stupid, but I mean...

19:15.363 --> 19:19.408
You know, come on, Howard,
the kid would have been smoking it anyway.

19:22.078 --> 19:23.704
I’m really sorry.

19:24.789 --> 19:28.084
This is urgent. Please excuse me. Hello.

19:45.601 --> 19:46.601
Fuck it.

20:23.764 --> 20:25.516
- Charlie?
- One sec.

20:28.227 --> 20:31.021
- Uh, my parents aren’t here.
- Is my wife here?

20:31.731 --> 20:32.773
I don’t see her.

20:35.985 --> 20:39.029
- Uh, how are you feeling?
- Awesome.

20:39.864 --> 20:41.699
Because you look okay.

20:41.991 --> 20:43.927
The way people were talking,
I thought maybe you were...

20:43.951 --> 20:46.537
Do you have like a balloon for me
or something?

20:46.620 --> 20:50.458
Yeah. In fact,
I thought you might like this.

20:51.292 --> 20:55.463
That’s pretty sweet.
What the fuck is this?

20:59.467 --> 21:00.551
Did you lift this?

21:01.677 --> 21:03.512
- No.
- You brought me a, uh...

21:03.804 --> 21:06.056
an erotic, stolen library book?

21:06.599 --> 21:07.933
Okay, I’ll take it.

21:08.100 --> 21:10.352
Hell no, it’s the best present
of all time. I love it!

21:11.729 --> 21:13.063
Okay. Um...

21:15.316 --> 21:18.652
If you need anything, I’ve moved,
so the number is on the back.

21:18.736 --> 21:22.740
What happened to you?
You quit your fancy job?

21:22.823 --> 21:24.867
Oh... Well, it’s complicated.

21:24.950 --> 21:29.079
But yeah. I couldn’t go on doing
what I was doing to make a living

21:29.163 --> 21:33.793
- and still feel good about myself.
- I can totally respect that.

21:35.085 --> 21:36.003
And it was complicated.

21:36.086 --> 21:38.172
There were a lot
of other things tied into it.

21:38.380 --> 21:42.802
Like my wife and the endless commuting
and just a lot of things.

21:42.885 --> 21:47.139
I couldn’t take it, so, uh...
Yeah... something had to change.

21:47.223 --> 21:50.017
I have to go to rehab now
because my parents are Nazi assholes.

21:50.100 --> 21:51.560
They’re worried about you.

21:51.644 --> 21:53.395
They’re embarrassed. There’s a difference.

21:53.479 --> 21:54.647
Well, you did a stupid thing.

21:55.231 --> 21:57.900
Seriously? I’m getting a lecture from you?
You were high as balls.

21:57.983 --> 22:00.986
I was tricked into that.
And, yeah, I’m sorry.

22:01.237 --> 22:04.323
- "Guys, I’m joyful. I feel joyful."
- Hey, hey, hey...

22:04.406 --> 22:07.409
I need you to, uh...
I need you to keep that between us.

22:07.660 --> 22:09.954
Don’t worry, I’m not gonna tell anyone.
It’s not my style.

22:11.205 --> 22:13.332
Hey, is that, uh... is that Laika?
Your drawing?

22:13.415 --> 22:15.042
It is. Do you know what the, uh,

22:15.125 --> 22:18.087
the scientist in charge of that project
said 40 years later? He said...

22:18.712 --> 22:20.965
"Nothing that we learned on that mission

22:21.048 --> 22:23.509
could possibly justify the loss
of that beautiful animal."

22:23.926 --> 22:26.595
She was a stray. He was the one
that found her in the first place.

22:28.097 --> 22:29.199
That’s heartbreaking.

22:29.223 --> 22:31.034
I know there’s already
a million books about her.

22:31.058 --> 22:32.418
Mine’s gonna have a different end.

22:32.643 --> 22:33.727
- Oh, yeah?
- So they said

22:34.019 --> 22:36.039
that she crashed into the ocean and died,
but she didn’t.

22:36.063 --> 22:37.773
She just burned alive in the atmosphere.

22:37.856 --> 22:40.150
So, in my version,
she’s supposed to still be out there.

22:40.234 --> 22:44.029
So Oleg, that’s the scientist guy,
is, like, old and poor,

22:44.321 --> 22:46.049
and one day he turns on some
of the old equipment,

22:46.073 --> 22:48.325
and he hears her heartbeat,
like she’s still out there.

22:48.534 --> 22:50.953
- What happens then?
- That’s as far as I’ve gotten.

22:52.955 --> 22:56.250
- Anders.
- He just brought me a book. That's it.

22:56.333 --> 22:58.961
Well, that was... sweet.

22:59.044 --> 23:01.630
I really admire him as an artist.

23:01.714 --> 23:04.758
- I really like his graphic novel.
- Yeah. So do I.

23:04.842 --> 23:07.553
- You don’t even know what it is.
- It’s about a dog.

23:07.636 --> 23:10.598
A stray dog, launched into space
for reasons she can never understand.

23:10.681 --> 23:11.849
It’s about being exploited

23:11.932 --> 23:14.226
by the people who are supposed
to be protecting you.

23:14.310 --> 23:16.103
The Meadows isn’t outer space, honey.

23:16.186 --> 23:17.855
It’s worse. It’s Arizona.

23:18.063 --> 23:19.207
You see what I have to deal with?

23:19.231 --> 23:21.191
I’m sorry, he needs to rest.

23:21.859 --> 23:24.486
- He’s here looking for his wife.
- Uh, no. Not, not true.

23:24.570 --> 23:25.738
I think she’s at home.

23:25.821 --> 23:27.197
With her new boyfriend?

23:27.281 --> 23:29.241
A lot of conversations
between my mom and your ex.

23:29.283 --> 23:31.410
You know, about whether things
are moving too fast.

23:31.493 --> 23:33.537
- A lot of yackety-yack.
- You made your point.

23:39.001 --> 23:40.753
- Feel better.
- Mm-hmm.

23:53.682 --> 23:56.602
<i>I know you’re not gonna pick up.
But I want some photo albums.</i>

23:56.894 --> 24:01.523
And I want, uh, some home movies,
because I have none here.

24:02.066 --> 24:04.026
Just a couple. Okay?

24:05.152 --> 24:09.531
I was full of bravado. I said,
"Yeah, sure. You want the house, keep it.

24:09.740 --> 24:10.616
Is that all you want?"

24:10.699 --> 24:12.660
I don’t know what the fuck I was thinking.

24:14.286 --> 24:16.997
You were thinking...
you were done with the marriage,

24:17.081 --> 24:18.624
so you were done with the house.

24:18.958 --> 24:19.958
I get that.

24:21.293 --> 24:23.879
So, I haven’t paid the mortgage
in six months.

24:24.546 --> 24:27.132
- So, what do you need?
- I’m gonna pay you back.

24:27.466 --> 24:30.010
- Every penny.
- I am not worried.

24:31.345 --> 24:32.346
You know...

24:33.138 --> 24:36.392
I used to have this vision of my life.

24:36.475 --> 24:37.768
It was like a web.

24:37.935 --> 24:42.106
And these threads
that connected me, you know.

24:42.189 --> 24:43.065
Yeah.

24:43.148 --> 24:46.485
And the more webs
you could have coming from you,

24:46.568 --> 24:48.570
then the more important you were. Right?

24:48.654 --> 24:51.156
Like, if you were a doctor
you’d cure a bunch of...

24:51.240 --> 24:52.116
- Patients.
- ...patients.

24:52.199 --> 24:54.034
And... or a teacher.

24:54.118 --> 24:56.245
You got a million threads, you know.

24:56.328 --> 24:59.665
And you would be, basically,
irreplaceable, right?

24:59.748 --> 25:02.292
'Cause so many people
depended on you, right?

25:02.376 --> 25:04.296
- You understand what I’m saying?
- Yeah, it's...

25:05.254 --> 25:07.631
- webs and...
- Yeah, but it’s really not the case.

25:07.715 --> 25:09.216
- Come on, man.
- No, it’s the web.

25:09.550 --> 25:12.928
The web is remaking itself.

25:13.554 --> 25:17.725
Revising itself every second of every day.
And so if you vanish,

25:17.808 --> 25:22.896
then the people that were in your life,
they learn to rely on someone else,

25:23.063 --> 25:24.982
you know, and you’re gone.

25:25.065 --> 25:29.945
And then the web just remakes itself
and moves on without you.

25:30.028 --> 25:32.614
- But you got out of the web.
- No, no, no.

25:32.698 --> 25:38.746
No. This whole town, it’s a life of work,
and commuting and bullshit.

25:39.621 --> 25:40.539
- Yeah.
- You know what I’m saying?

25:40.622 --> 25:43.917
And that was one web
I was happy to get out of.

25:44.918 --> 25:46.128
Just drink up.

25:51.383 --> 25:52.384
Come on. Come on, man.

25:53.218 --> 25:54.970
I think you need to see something.

26:18.786 --> 26:21.997
How’s Preston? He’s still at Northwestern?

26:22.539 --> 26:24.625
Graduated. Living with Helene.

26:24.708 --> 26:27.544
Oh, Jesus. What was the point?

26:39.556 --> 26:40.556
Miss that?

26:47.606 --> 26:51.735
I’m taking this Asian fusion
cooking class.

26:52.110 --> 26:53.028
Total blast.

26:53.111 --> 26:57.115
I never would have thought
cooking is so relaxing.

26:57.366 --> 26:59.409
You know, I just put on some music,

26:59.576 --> 27:01.870
sip some wine, a few hours go by,

27:02.120 --> 27:03.997
end up with a delicious meal.

27:05.624 --> 27:09.336
I generally eat it alone,
but it’s delicious. Delicious!

27:09.419 --> 27:12.422
Larry, it's... Don’t you think
it’s a little tragic?

27:12.589 --> 27:15.676
Fuck you, man.
Only if you look at it that way.

27:15.759 --> 27:18.846
- It’s how you see it. It's how you see it.
- Hi, guys.

27:18.929 --> 27:20.722
- How about a dance?
- No, thank you.

27:21.014 --> 27:23.725
- Are you sure?
- Yeah. Yeah, no offense.

27:23.809 --> 27:24.809
Come on.

27:24.852 --> 27:27.437
- He’s newly divorced, so...
- Oh!

27:27.521 --> 27:31.108
- Then you need a little extra TLC.
- You’re probably right, but uh...

27:33.569 --> 27:37.823
- I’ll take the dance.
- Okay. You got it.

27:43.036 --> 27:44.288
You okay, dude?

27:46.123 --> 27:49.793
Hey, could you, uh,
wet a paper towel for me, please?

27:51.753 --> 27:53.380
Am I in the men’s room?

28:05.601 --> 28:06.727
Thank you.

28:13.191 --> 28:14.359
You okay?

28:15.444 --> 28:17.946
I haven’t thrown up in a club
since I was 22.

28:18.196 --> 28:20.436
- I wouldn’t drink that if I were you.
- It's disgusting.

28:20.991 --> 28:22.367
Oh. Yeah. Right.

28:23.160 --> 28:25.746
- Why are you here?
- Why are you here?

28:25.913 --> 28:26.913
No, why are you here?

28:28.916 --> 28:32.502
I was stupid enough
to come here on a date.

28:35.213 --> 28:36.715
Oh, my God...

28:37.132 --> 28:40.093
Yeah, I’m hip. I can go to a strip club.

28:41.053 --> 28:43.722
Three vodkas in, he’s trying to buy me
a fucking lap dance.

28:43.805 --> 28:46.725
Is it hip for a woman
to go to a strip club?

28:47.434 --> 28:48.434
I don’t know.

28:50.562 --> 28:53.899
Well, if it makes you feel any better,
I didn’t want to come here, either.

28:56.318 --> 28:57.402
Yeah, right.

29:04.368 --> 29:06.245
Hey, man,
I think your friend went upstairs.

29:06.411 --> 29:09.122
- Oh, thank you.
- Yeah.

29:31.144 --> 29:32.271
Okay?

29:32.896 --> 29:33.896
Thank you.

29:42.990 --> 29:45.367
42 Maple Street, please.

29:45.534 --> 29:48.829
And 112 Fisherman’s Lane.

29:48.912 --> 29:51.164
I don’t have enough money.

29:51.957 --> 29:53.458
Don’t worry about it. I got it.

29:54.626 --> 29:55.626
Thank you.

30:02.843 --> 30:03.843
Beautiful house.

30:06.263 --> 30:07.389
Why are we here?

30:07.556 --> 30:10.600
112 Fisherman’s Lane.
That’s what you said.

30:16.606 --> 30:17.649
Well...

30:21.111 --> 30:23.655
- Uh... Here. Take care.
- Oh. Thank you.

30:58.190 --> 31:00.901
What the hell is all this shit?

31:13.955 --> 31:17.417
Who the fuck is in my house?
Jesus Christ, Anders!

31:17.918 --> 31:20.478
- I almost took your fucking head off.
- What are you doing here?

31:20.504 --> 31:23.882
You know what? I’m just getting some
things of mine. Everyone needs to relax.

31:24.257 --> 31:25.342
This is a weird flavor.

31:25.509 --> 31:28.553
- Are you kidding me?
- Nope. Tastes like... flowers.

31:28.637 --> 31:29.757
You can’t just come in here!

31:29.805 --> 31:31.890
I’m getting some things
that are rightfully mine.

31:31.973 --> 31:34.101
- No, you’re drunk.
- Some of this stuff...

31:34.643 --> 31:36.645
I have a right to have it in my house.

31:36.728 --> 31:40.482
I left a whole box of stuff for you,
over here by the door.

31:40.774 --> 31:43.402
- Then what’s all this?
- I gave you half!

31:47.739 --> 31:50.534
Oh. Okay. Sorry.

31:50.700 --> 31:52.220
You care so much about family pictures,

31:52.244 --> 31:54.329
you need to break in here
in the middle of the night.

31:57.207 --> 31:59.918
- What's wrong with you?
- Well, I am a little dizzy.

32:00.001 --> 32:02.379
- Why don’t you take a seat?
- Don’t tell me what to do.

32:02.754 --> 32:04.589
I’m gonna sit down anyway.

32:07.968 --> 32:09.636
Why don’t you give me those keys?

32:10.303 --> 32:11.680
Donny, don’t do this now.

32:11.763 --> 32:13.515
We can’t have this happen again. Come on.

32:13.598 --> 32:15.600
You’re not going to do this again,
right, Dad?

32:18.103 --> 32:19.438
You know what?

32:20.439 --> 32:21.606
You never know.

32:24.359 --> 32:26.653
Preston, can you drive
your father home, please?

32:27.779 --> 32:28.822
You got it.

32:36.204 --> 32:38.248
So, she hired you.

32:38.748 --> 32:40.917
'Cause I thought it was all volunteers.

32:41.001 --> 32:44.129
Yeah, most of them are,
but she worked it out so I could get paid.

32:44.212 --> 32:45.714
Takes a lot of patience.

32:45.964 --> 32:47.883
- You like it?
- Yeah. The pay is shit, but...

32:47.966 --> 32:49.843
But you’re saving for your own place?

32:51.970 --> 32:54.139
It’s not that bad. I gotta go.

32:54.222 --> 32:55.515
- Where?
- Work.

32:55.891 --> 32:56.891
Oh.

32:58.226 --> 33:00.979
Hey, Preston. Come back here.

33:01.396 --> 33:03.440
What does she see in him?

33:06.359 --> 33:07.694
I don’t know. I mean...

33:08.403 --> 33:10.697
- They seem kind of happy.
- Bullshit.

33:11.448 --> 33:12.741
You know, you left her.

33:13.200 --> 33:14.993
Right? You remember that?

33:15.076 --> 33:16.411
You’re mad at me about that.

33:16.495 --> 33:20.040
No, I’m totally thrilled you just kicked
Mom to the curb after all this time.

33:20.123 --> 33:22.918
I’m gonna apologize to her
about last night, but...

33:26.171 --> 33:27.172
I worry about you.

33:27.464 --> 33:30.258
- You’re worried about me?
- Yeah. I can be an idiot

33:30.342 --> 33:33.512
and I can still worry about you.

33:34.971 --> 33:37.807
Okay, now, Christmas Eve,
why don’t you come over?

33:37.891 --> 33:41.811
We’ll hang out. You can stay over,
we’ll watch some videos, or...

33:42.479 --> 33:46.483
Mom’s planning the usual dinner.
Like she does every year, so I’m sorry.

33:46.566 --> 33:49.152
But she’s already
making a big deal out of it.

33:49.236 --> 33:50.946
Yeah, don’t worry about it. It’s nothing.

33:51.446 --> 33:54.032
Okay, go teach someone how to read.

33:54.199 --> 33:55.951
- All right, I will.
- Cool.

33:58.286 --> 33:59.913
So, uh, Mr. Baptiste,

33:59.996 --> 34:03.875
I understand there has been a dispute
with your tutor.

34:03.959 --> 34:05.210
It’s not a dispute.

34:05.293 --> 34:06.878
If you would explain everything to me.

34:06.962 --> 34:09.380
- He stole from me.
- He stole from you? How?

34:09.464 --> 34:12.217
Your son told me about an opportunity
to make money.

34:12.425 --> 34:14.553
An opportunity?
What kind of an opportunity?

34:14.636 --> 34:16.304
Some gambling business.

34:16.596 --> 34:19.599
How he’s going to double my money.
Where’s my money?

34:20.058 --> 34:21.058
I don’t see it.

34:21.101 --> 34:22.393
I need this money.

34:28.817 --> 34:32.487
Hey, I’m, uh...
I'm Anders. I’m your neighbor.

34:33.154 --> 34:34.154
Hello.

34:34.281 --> 34:35.281
Hello.

34:38.201 --> 34:42.414
Oh, look... Look, hold on. Hold on.
No, no, no, you’re missing the best part.

34:47.835 --> 34:48.670
Come in.

34:48.753 --> 34:50.130
Hey.

34:50.797 --> 34:51.797
Okay...

34:53.091 --> 34:57.470
I was drunk. Uh, it was a stupid,
obviously ridiculous thing to do.

34:57.554 --> 34:58.847
- I’m sorry.
- Terrific, Anders.

34:58.930 --> 35:02.267
At the moment,
I need to find our moron of a son

35:02.684 --> 35:05.937
who fucked up the only job he could get
because his mother gave it to him.

35:06.313 --> 35:07.731
Where is he?

35:08.064 --> 35:09.566
I have an idea.

35:09.774 --> 35:12.569
How could he do this to me? To himself?

35:13.194 --> 35:15.196
Hold on, do what?

35:15.280 --> 35:18.366
He took money from a client
and gambled with it.

35:29.628 --> 35:33.923
Hi. Is there a, uh, poker game
going on here somewhere?

35:34.633 --> 35:36.259
- Excuse me.
- I’m not causing trouble.

35:36.343 --> 35:39.304
I’m just, uh, looking for my son.

35:42.182 --> 35:43.182
Through the kitchen.

35:59.282 --> 36:02.035
This is very impressive.
Did you guys have me followed?

36:02.911 --> 36:04.371
Wow, Preston. Really?

36:06.665 --> 36:08.750
I had a very
interesting conversation today.

36:08.833 --> 36:10.335
I didn’t take that guy's money.

36:10.752 --> 36:13.254
$2,000 from an illiterate man.

36:13.797 --> 36:15.840
I thought we weren’t supposed
to use that word.

36:15.924 --> 36:17.092
Don’t be an asshole, Preston.

36:17.175 --> 36:19.135
Look, I’m going to win it back. Okay?

36:21.596 --> 36:23.890
Look at you two, a real team.

36:25.016 --> 36:27.620
- Do you want to tell me what happened?
- Yeah, he gave me the money.

36:27.644 --> 36:29.479
- For you to gamble with?
- The guy...

36:30.230 --> 36:31.870
he had a broken truck and he was thinking

36:31.898 --> 36:35.068
about asking some sketchy dude
in the neighborhood for a loan, okay?

36:35.151 --> 36:36.462
I told him how these things work,

36:36.486 --> 36:38.905
how he’d get himself curb-stomped
if he’s not careful.

36:39.114 --> 36:41.032
So he asked if I knew of anything else...

36:41.241 --> 36:42.909
And you thought, "Oh, that’s right,

36:42.992 --> 36:45.352
there’s that underground poker game
that I’m involved with."

36:45.412 --> 36:47.205
Okay. Let’s just get this over with.

36:47.288 --> 36:50.375
- Get what over with?
- The firing. The sacking. Come on.

36:50.750 --> 36:52.627
- I get it.
- You have to understand, Preston,

36:52.711 --> 36:56.673
even if you meant well, it’s gonna look
really bad if I don’t fire you.

36:57.382 --> 36:59.217
You don’t have to explain it.

36:59.759 --> 37:00.759
You’re fired.

37:01.845 --> 37:04.222
- And you have a week to move out.
- All right.

37:05.223 --> 37:07.767
Oh, uh, but you should probably
look for a place to live, too.

37:07.934 --> 37:09.161
Me? What is that supposed to mean?

37:09.185 --> 37:11.020
Well, 'cause
Dad’s not paying the mortgage.

37:11.521 --> 37:13.398
- He hasn’t in six months.
- So...

37:13.857 --> 37:16.317
You’re still fired.
And you’re still moving out.

37:23.700 --> 37:25.785
- Look...
- Just tell me that that’s not true.

37:25.869 --> 37:27.370
I’m getting it sorted...

37:27.454 --> 37:31.166
You had to be a big man, right?
"Go ahead. Keep the house."

37:31.499 --> 37:34.252
I was attempting to be... generous.

37:34.335 --> 37:38.131
The only problem, Anders, is to be
a big man, you have to be a big man.

37:38.214 --> 37:42.594
I made so much money for everybody!
Everybody! For years!

37:42.677 --> 37:44.888
So I could lose the house. To foreclosure.

37:45.096 --> 37:48.391
Why do you even want it?
It's a five-bedroom house.

37:48.516 --> 37:50.310
Look, I may decide to move.

37:50.602 --> 37:54.606
But if I decide to move,
I prefer that it’s my choice.

37:54.773 --> 37:57.108
Well, you don’t have to worry
'cause I’m getting the money.

37:57.192 --> 37:58.485
Really? And how?

37:58.568 --> 38:00.612
A loan. From Larry Eichner.

38:01.237 --> 38:04.824
That house is our history.

38:05.116 --> 38:08.828
It’s my history.
I made that garden from nothing.

38:08.912 --> 38:10.872
- And that means something.
- I know.

38:11.164 --> 38:12.415
I know it means something.

38:12.499 --> 38:15.835
But do you really?
Do you know what anything means?

38:18.213 --> 38:19.255
I thought I did.

38:21.716 --> 38:25.720
You’re supposed to be happy now, Anders.
That’s why we got divorced, right?

38:25.804 --> 38:29.224
'Cause we were all in the way
of your happiness.

38:29.307 --> 38:32.811
The house, your career, me.
The way of life.

38:33.186 --> 38:34.896
- You remember all that?
- Yeah.

39:07.887 --> 39:09.514
- I’m the lady who...
- I recognize you.

39:09.722 --> 39:11.516
- We shared a cab.
- Feeling better?

39:11.599 --> 39:12.684
Yeah, thank you.

39:13.434 --> 39:14.853
Listen, that cab was a fortune.

39:14.936 --> 39:16.288
- Let me pay you back.
- Oh, God, no.

39:16.312 --> 39:17.730
- Oh, no, I insist.
- No, come on.

39:18.523 --> 39:20.608
Can I buy you lunch or something?

39:21.651 --> 39:23.319
Okay, don’t worry about it. I just...

39:23.403 --> 39:25.363
I just wanted you to know
I appreciated it.

39:25.446 --> 39:28.283
You really saved me. And I thank you.

39:28.825 --> 39:30.493
You know what? Yeah.

39:31.452 --> 39:35.206
Yeah, buy me lunch.
A very, very expensive lunch.

39:35.373 --> 39:36.374
Okay.

39:36.875 --> 39:38.668
Would you please put your number in there?

39:43.047 --> 39:45.717
All I ask. Please don’t fucking text me.

39:47.969 --> 39:52.015
I’ll text you soon. Yeah?

40:06.279 --> 40:08.072
- Hey.
- Okay...

40:08.156 --> 40:11.284
- Is this a bad time?
- Uh, no. Were you waiting for me?

40:11.910 --> 40:15.079
- No. Just drove up.
- Okay. I just got home. Uh...

40:15.163 --> 40:16.414
- Yeah, come in.
- Great.

40:17.498 --> 40:18.498
Wow!

40:19.792 --> 40:20.710
This is a nice place.

40:20.793 --> 40:23.504
Oh. Thank you. Well, it’s not,
not as nice as yours, but...

40:27.342 --> 40:28.968
Uh, how about a beer?

40:29.594 --> 40:30.970
No. Definitely not.

40:32.764 --> 40:35.058
Listen. I’d like to apologize.

40:36.434 --> 40:37.518
- You?
- Yeah. Yeah.

